1.formula: Your dashboard represents a one page picture of what the problem is - what the solution is - what market segment you are going to pursue - and why. If you found competition or complimentary products, your observations in this area are the most important.  You learn something about the market that you did not know and wish to revisit the problem/ solution hypotheses to integrate that information. You may end up completely restating the problem, or the solution, and you should, as long as the research you have performed supports those changes. Alternatively - you may have demonstrated by the research that you are on the right track and you should continue to discover the customer segments for this PSet. See you in Loop2!
